== Installing CMake ==
1) Download CMake from: http://www.cmake.org/cmake/resources/software.html
2) To install, follow instructions from: http://www.cmake.org/cmake/help/install.html

== Installing YARP ==
1) To install YARP follow instructions from: http://eris.liralab.it/yarpdoc/install.html

== Installing the iCub Simulator ==
1) To install the simulator, follow the instructions from: http://eris.liralab.it/wiki/ICub_Simulator_Installation

== Installing Boost ==
1) Get and install the latest Boost package from: http://www.boost.org/users/download/

== Compiling the libraries ==

1) Empty the contents of the "build" subdirectory
2) Set the "build" subdirectory as your current directory (eg. cd)
3) Run "cmake ../" with the appropriate platform flags, eg "cmake.exe" -G "MinGW Makefiles" ../ if you are using MinGW under Windows
4) Run "make" in the make directory. To compile documentation, run "make doxygen"
